regarded than are the <HI>Copies</HI> of the <HI>Dialogues</HI> between <HI>Pasquin</HI> and <HI>Marpho|rio</HI>
that come here, I have deliberately Surveyed it and done it what right
I could. And by occasion hereof do here call to mind a <HI>Remark</HI> on the
<HI>Papacy</HI> I met with in a <HI>Pamphlet</HI> of one of our <HI>Dissenters,</HI> viz. <HI>That if
the Pope were a good man, he might do a great deal of good.</HI></P>
<P>Tho for sometime after I had begun this <HI>Discourse,</HI> I was somewhat a
Stranger to the great Character of the present Pope, (and so continued
