great States-man <HI>Chichley</HI> Archbishop of <HI>Canterbury,</HI> in a <HI>Letter</HI> to Pope <HI>Mar|tine</HI>
the Fifth, Complain'd, <HI>That there were then so many here in</HI> England <HI>in|fected
with the heresies of</HI> Wicliff <HI>and</HI> Husse, <HI>that without force of an Army they
could not be supprest:</HI> Whereupon the <HI>Pope</HI> sent two Cardinals to the Arch-Bishop
to Cause a <HI>Tenth</HI> to be gather'd of all Spiritual and Religious men,
