<P>Many of the Scholars of the University of <HI>Oxford</HI> did <HI>mutinously</HI> oppose
the introducing the knowledge of the <HI>Greek</HI> Tongue there, and were there|upon
call'd <HI>Trojans,</HI> and others of the Schollars were as <HI>rohust</HI> and loud for
<PB N="72" REF="88">
that Language, who were therefore called <HI>Graecians:</HI> but by a <HI>Letter</HI> w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">it by
<HI>Sir Thomas More</HI> to that University and by the Kings Command (which Let|ter
