absolute temporal power on the stage of the Kingdom, they would be too apt
with Mr. <HI>Hobs</HI> to thrust the whole Nation of Spiritual Beings out of the
world; I mean rather then they would be to their faces cheated and harras'd
by a spiritual power: and our people inspir'd with witt as well as those
with the zealous spirit of Religion would cry out, <HI>conclusum est contra Ma|nichaeos;
I,</HI> and against the <HI>Schoolmen</HI> too, I mean our Romanist <HI>Manichaei</HI>
who make two <HI>summa Principia</HI> in every State.</P>
<P>In this age where the lower or Sixth <HI>rate</HI> Witts do so over-value them|selves
on turning every thing into <HI>ridicule,</HI> the Mass would have here a Re|ception
according to what the <HI>gloss</HI> in the <HI>Canon</HI> Law observes, <HI>that when a
