to us as <HI>Matthew Paris</HI> called it of old, <HI>barathrum proventuum.</HI></P>
<P><PB N="80" REF="92">
And any who considers that his Majesty hath not without difficulty
obtain'd <HI>Supplies</HI> of Mony from late <HI>Parliaments,</HI> and that they
have been all <HI>appropriated</HI> to certain publick uses, may well give the
