<PB N="88" REF="96">
the World, then that poor <HI>Hermit Fryer</HI> Martin Luther <HI>scourged the</HI> Popes
<HI>Buyers and Sellers out of the Temple,</HI> with as much ease almost as our <HI>Savi|our</HI>
did the <HI>Iewish.</HI></P>
<P>Any one who shall consider the burden of <HI>Oblations,</HI> that the devoute<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
Roman Catholicks in <HI>England</HI> lye under, as to their <HI>Priests</HI> (which we may
