'tis said in the <HI>Digests, In fraudem legis facit qui salvis verbis le|gis,
sententiam ejus circumvenit.</HI></P>
<P>But this in the Case of an <HI>Oath</HI> was more abominated, and accordingly
<HI>Cicero</HI> tells us, that <HI>Fraus adstringit non dissolvit perjurium.</HI> And if the
<HI>Civil</HI> Law was afterward so provident for the honour of Humane Na|ture
