of discharging any Future <HI>Dues</HI> successively, and (as I said) <HI>reddendo
singula singulis,</HI> to be familiar enough to common thought and vulgar
apprehensions, and likewise the word <HI>Heirs</HI> to be so too.</P>
<P>The many who take the <HI>Oaths</HI> of <HI>Allegiance</HI> and <HI>Supremacy</HI> have spent
enough time, and perhaps too much ventured eternity, in thinking of and
providing for their <HI>Heirs;</HI> and who commonly as <HI>landed</HI> men know that
